## Q1: Free short-sleeve bowling/polo jersey GLB — VERDICT: NONE suitable

Vetting results:
- **pmndrs/drei-assets `shirt_baked_collapsed.glb`** (the most-cited free shirt):
  - URL: `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pmndrs/drei-assets/master/shirt_baked_collapsed.glb` — T-shirt (round neck, no placket, no sleeves). UVs: single front island U≈0.27–0.73, back = remaining U wrap. Style wrong for bowlifi mandarin/button requirement.
- **Poly Pizza CC0** — no bowling-style jersey found; mostly polos/rounds. Even the best candidate would need collar/placket sculpting we cannot do at runtime.
- **Khronos Sample Models** — no apparel, industrial/vehicle focus.
- **Sketchfab CC0 filter "bowling shirt"** — models exist but are hi-poly (>5MB), no documented UV layout, inconsistent licensing metadata.

**Decision: commit to procedural volumetric fallback.** The bowlifi style (mandarin collar, button placket, set-in sleeves) is not achievable with any available free GLB within scope. The procedural mesh gives exact control of UV layout for the wrap requirement.

Procedural mesh recipe (CylinderGeometry body + sleeve/collar primitives):
- Body: `CylinderGeometry(0.38, 0.32, 1.0, 48, 8)` (slight taper, 48 radial segments for smooth wrap)
- U naturally runs 0→1 around the circumference; seams = at U=0 (right underarm, hidden)
- Front panel: U 0.25→0.75, V 0.1→0.95 (center half, shirt front visible when facing camera)
- Back panel: U 0.75→1.25 (via RepeatWrapping) — same V range
- Sleeves: `CylinderGeometry(0.15, 0.12, 0.35, 24)`, rotated, own UV region or simple tint-only material
- Collar: flat torus segment, color-only material (no image island needed)
- Button placket: `PlaneGeometry` overlay strip, color-only

