- produced: answers to Q1–Q5 — no free jersey GLB exists (commit to procedural volumetric CylinderGeometry); fabric material recipe (meshPhysicalMaterial params + Environment preset + Poly Haven normal map URL); smart-align stack (@imgly/background-removal lazy WASM + deterministic alpha-bbox fallback with pseudocode); single CanvasTexture UV island layout (pixel coordinates for 2048px canvas); seamless wrap technique (ClampToEdge + seam at U=0 underarm).
- decisions: procedural mesh locked in (no GLB); @imgly/background-removal for optional refine (lazy import, ~12MB, static-hostable, WASM); deterministic alpha-bbox is always-on <10ms; single CanvasTexture with FRONT island at canvas pixels 512–1536 and BACK split at 0–512 + 1536–2048; Poly Haven knit_fabric_02 normal map for fabric realism.
- next needs: planner flips PLAN-STATUS to ready with geometry=procedural confirmed. Demo-builder: (1) swap ShirtCanvas to CylinderGeometry body + sleeve/collar primitives; (2) add compositor.ts with the UV island pixel layout above; (3) add smartAlign.ts with alpha-bbox + lazy @imgly import; (4) load Poly Haven normal map URL into meshPhysicalMaterial; (5) add OptionsPanel upload slots + toggle + sliders; (6) adjust Decal position to cylinder radius.
- risks: @imgly/background-removal CDN model fetch may be slow on first use (~12MB) — mitigate by showing "analyzing..." spinner and applying deterministic result instantly while model loads; Poly Haven CDN URL may require CORS check at build time; CylinderGeometry collar/placket styling is geometry-only (no UV detail) so button/mandarin detail depends on geometry + material fidelity, not texture.
